result.execSummary:
The defendant Bobby Joe Grady was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Bobby Joe Grady in court with attorney Darryl Everett Smith.  Defendant Bobby Joe Grady in custody.  Kimberly Dorice Schoepp appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
As to the charged offense:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, and plead GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty. Judgment of conviction entered.
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the state, defense and defendant.
The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 183 days  in the House of Correction, with credit for 183 days time served.  
Court sets restitution at ZERO.
The court orders defendant to pay all applicable costs, fees, assessments and surcharges, DNA sample and surcharge by 2-17-2017 and failure to do so will result in entry of civil judgment.
